08:55.160 --> 08:56.275
LEM:
Police.

08:57.200 --> 08:58.679
[GRUNTING]

08:58.880 --> 09:00.757
On the ground.

09:04.040 --> 09:06.190
VIC:
Couple of your crew
caught dirt naps today.

09:06.400 --> 09:08.630
I'm thinking you Bop Street boys
are policing yourselves.

09:08.840 --> 09:09.909
You're tripping, man.

09:10.120 --> 09:11.553
Then why were they
rolling with Kasper?

09:11.760 --> 09:12.954
We all right with Kasper, mostly.

09:13.160 --> 09:15.390
As in you wanted him
and his crew mostly dead,

09:15.600 --> 09:17.431
or you beefing with
some other set?

09:17.640 --> 09:18.595
I don't know.

09:18.800 --> 09:20.199
This guy's rank and file.

09:20.400 --> 09:22.197
RONNIE:
Look what I found.

09:23.720 --> 09:27.030
We been letting Bop Street run game
as long as you kept it low-key.

09:27.240 --> 09:28.389
Truce is over.

09:28.600 --> 09:32.036
You tell Gunsmoke I'm gonna
shut down a Bop Street
rock house every two hours

09:32.240 --> 09:33.639
until I get that shooter.

09:33.840 --> 09:36.149
SHANE:
Your clique, rival set,
doesn't matter.

09:36.360 --> 09:37.315
We want a name.

09:37.520 --> 09:39.351
Nice touch. Crack vials.
That's old school.

09:39.920 --> 09:44.152
A name by the end of today
or Bop Street can start
filing for Chapter 11.

09:47.440 --> 09:49.396
DUTCH:
Uh, no. Thank you.

09:50.800 --> 09:52.756
Well, what do you know.

09:53.640 --> 09:55.119
Robbery-Homicide.

09:55.320 --> 09:58.471
Seems they're sniffing around the
Dutch man, wanna set up an interview.

09:59.320 --> 10:01.629
That's impressive,
elite of the elite.

10:01.840 --> 10:03.956
Well, it's not a total surprise.

10:04.160 --> 10:07.197
We've closed some big ones,
the whole business with
the DA's behind us.

10:07.400 --> 10:08.958
I guess we got some buzz.

10:09.640 --> 10:11.790
You, anyway.

10:12.880 --> 10:14.836
Hey, isn't that, uh?

10:16.520 --> 10:18.272
CLAUDETTE:
Fatima Gardner.

10:18.480 --> 10:21.040
It's Kleavon's sister.
Yeah.

10:21.240 --> 10:24.471
You all were pretty sure Kleavon
killed that girl back when.

10:24.680 --> 10:28.195
Lana Gregory. Her and several others,
we just weren't able to prove it.

10:28.400 --> 10:31.949
I've been doing what you said,
watching and listening.

10:32.160 --> 10:34.833
And I found this while
I was cleaning his room.

10:35.040 --> 10:37.031
It's Kleavon's.

10:37.240 --> 10:39.037
DUTCH:
That's a lot of blood.

10:39.240 --> 10:41.071
We'II, uh... We'll check this for DNA.

10:41.280 --> 10:43.271
FATIMA:
I don't know if he's
noticed it's missing.

10:43.480 --> 10:46.040
