security work on the side?

14:26.440 --> 14:29.671
Mara's a realtor.
Between our two salaries,
we make do.

14:31.360 --> 14:35.239
Reason I'm here is I wanna
nail shut the Terry Crowley file.

14:35.480 --> 14:37.198
I see that.

14:37.960 --> 14:40.872
That happened over two
years ago. IAD cleared us.

14:41.080 --> 14:43.594
Or didn't you hear the squeaks
in your rat hole?

14:44.320 --> 14:46.834
Wonder if you'd mind taking
a look at a transcript

14:47.040 --> 14:50.157
of your interview after
the, uh, shooting.

14:50.360 --> 14:52.351
See if it jars anything new loose.

14:52.560 --> 14:55.199
I've been looking at
your jacket. Wow.

14:56.520 --> 14:58.033
Pretty effective cop.

14:58.240 --> 15:01.596
Gotten yourself into a couple of
sketchy situations along the way.

15:01.800 --> 15:03.836
Black mark or two.

15:04.920 --> 15:06.911
You were on your own
for a while last year.

15:07.120 --> 15:10.715
Vice. What made you come
back to the Strike Team?

15:10.960 --> 15:15.272
I would think that you
would wanna make a name
for yourself flying solo.

15:15.480 --> 15:19.473
Like you dribbling shit all over us
to make a name for yourself?

15:20.320 --> 15:21.548
All the same,

15:21.760 --> 15:23.876
living in Mackey's shadow
all the time?

15:26.280 --> 15:29.636
You don't feel that he was trying
to get you back into the fold

15:29.840 --> 15:32.479
so that he could get
a leash on you, do you?

15:35.360 --> 15:37.669
What's here is how
it went down.

15:39.880 --> 15:44.396
So there was just you, Vic,

15:44.880 --> 15:48.190
Terry and Two-Time in that room?

15:48.400 --> 15:50.072
Just me and Vic.

15:50.760 --> 15:52.876
No Lemansky, no Gardocki?

15:53.080 --> 15:56.516
It was true then, it's true now.

15:58.320 --> 16:00.072
Thanks so much for your help.

16:01.200 --> 16:03.191
I'm gonna need you
to sign a document

16:03.400 --> 16:07.632
confirming that you know that we are
reopening the Terry Crowley case

16:07.840 --> 16:09.796
and you are under investigation.

16:11.400 --> 16:13.152
Blow me.

16:19.920 --> 16:21.911
CLAUDETTE:
I've talked to every
precinct in the city.

16:22.120 --> 16:24.873
No recent bodies matching
Kleavon's m.o.

16:26.520 --> 16:28.590
You gonna do something with that?

16:29.440 --> 16:31.556
Just got off the phone
with Robbery-Homicide.

16:31.760 --> 16:33.352
Turns out they didn't
just find me.

16:33.560 --> 16:37.792
A "veteran detective"
recommended they
review my file?

16:38.000 --> 16:39.718
I'm gonna check
Missing Persons again.

16:39.920 --> 16:40.955
Are you trying to get rid of me?

16:41.160 --> 16:42.991
I thought Robbery-Homicide
was your dream job.

16:43.200 --> 16:45.919
I didn't need your help.
There is buzz.

16:46.120 --> 16:49.271
Hey, you guys have a Fatima Gardner
sign in to see you this morning?

16:49.520 --> 16:50.873
Yeah.

16:51.080 --> 16:53.116
Her brother just
reported her missing.

17:01.040 --> 17:03.076
Yeah?
Captain left a few things up here.

17:03.280 --> 17:04.713
He asked me to get them.

17:04.920 --> 17:07.387
Sure. Anything you need.

17:10.960 --> 17:13.713
I pulled this off
the wall downstairs.

17:13.920 --> 17:15.876
Pretty demeaning,
don't you think?

17:16.079 --> 17:18.992
Doesn't really bother me.
Just boys being boys.

17:19.200 --> 17:21.760
A lot of money on Vic
being your baby's daddy.

17:21.960 --> 17:23.551
Everybody's got an opinion.

17:23.760 --> 17:25.715
Heard a lot of rumours
about the two of you.

17:25.920 --> 17:28.673
Are you saying that
they aren't true?

17:28.880 --> 17:30.871
Look, I'm sure you
won't blame me

17:31.080 --> 17:34.789
when I don't discuss stupid gossip
about my personal life with IAD.

17:35.480 --> 17:37.436
Sexual relationships between
department personnel

17:37.640 --> 17:39.790
need to be divulged
in a timely manner

17:40.000 --> 17:41.752
according to the
employee handbook.

17:41.960 --> 17:44.997
Failure to do so can
result in suspensions,

17:45.200 --> 17:47.031
even demotions.

17:48.320 --> 17:51.517
You just got a pay bump
recently, didn't you?

17:51.720 --> 17:54.996
Come on, there's no relationship
between me and Vic.

17:56.240 --> 17:59.789
Should I make this official?

18:00.000 --> 18:05.074
Because I can do that,
widen my investigation.

18:07.680 --> 18:09.238
[DANNY SIGHS]

18:11.360 --> 18:13.920
Vic and I had a thing, okay?
It's in the past.

18:14.120 --> 18:15.712
When was that?

18:16.440 --> 18:17.555
Eight or nine months ago?

18:17.760 --> 18:20.149
You wanna get a court order
to draw blood, go right ahead.

18:20.360 --> 18:21.759
But this is none of
your business.

18:21.960 --> 18:24.838
You still have to disclose
your relationship with Mackey.

18:25.040 --> 18:26.996
Fill out the forms today

18:27.200 --> 18:29.270
and I'll overlook the tardiness.

18:30.720 --> 18:33.280
Hey, Vic. Checked out our next
Bop Street target on Hoover.

18:33.720 --> 18:34.914
Doors and windows are fortified.

18:35.120 --> 18:37.395
All right, have Ronnie get a
doorknocker. Flash-bangs too.

18:37.600 --> 18:38.749
All right, man.

18:38.960 --> 18:41.633
VIC: Hey. Hang on.
OFFICER: Over there.

18:44.960 --> 18:48.953
Gunsmoke. We were just about
to pay a visit to another one
of your crack palaces.

18:49.160 --> 18:50.912
Look, man, I don't know
who capped my peoples,

18:51.120 --> 18:53.395
but I tell you straight up, it
wasn't no Bop Street niggers.

18:53.600 --> 18:56.239
After Hoover we're gonna stop by
your Temple Street smoke house.

18:56.440 --> 18:58.590
That'll bring your one-day loss
to what, 12 K?

18:58.800 --> 19:01.951
You know what it does
to my street cred even
walking into this pig farm?

19:02.160 --> 19:04.037
Oink when you got
something we can use.

19:04.240 --> 19:06.708
Hold up, hold up, hold up.
Come here.

19:08.160 --> 19:09.957
Tell him.

19:10.560 --> 19:12.516
I'm chilling at homegirl's
around the way,

19:12.720 --> 19:14.756
hear shots, see these
two vatos drive off.

19:14.960 --> 19:16.996
What did they look like?
Vatos.

19:17.200 --> 19:19.839
You know, shaved heads,
white tees.

19:20.040 --> 19:22.190
Guy driving had "L.A."
tattooed all up in here.

19:22.400 --> 19:24.311
But I didn't get a look
at the dude shooting.

19:24.520 --> 19:26.590
LEM: What kind of car?
Old, I don't know.

19:26.800 --> 19:27.949
[SCOFFS]

19:28.160 --> 19:31.197
But they was riding on
gold-anodised hundred-spoke D's.

19:32.440 --> 19:33.634
I know my wheels.

19:34.040 --> 19:35.951
So we straight now?
VIC: Not yet.

19:36.160 --> 19:39.835
How's a punk-ass wigger
like Kasper get respect from
a crew hard as Bop Street?

19:40.040 --> 19:42.395
Thought he was a poser
myself for a minute.

19:42.600 --> 19:44.192
White boy got business skills.

19:44.400 --> 19:47.756
Splits fifty-fifty off top,
so folks are getting paid.

19:47.960 --> 19:49.916
Come with these names
for the product:

19:50.120 --> 19:51.792
Pink Yo, Yellow Fever.

19:52.000 --> 19:53.752
Same old shit, only
different coloured caps.

19:54.280 --> 19:57.078
You're moving Kasper's
product out of the place we
took down this morning?

19:57.280 --> 19:59.396
GUNSMOKE:
Look, man, fiends want
what Kasper's selling.

19:59.600 --> 20:02.034
Can't argue with
the free market.

20:02.240 --> 20:04.390
Looking forward to
that truce again, fellas.

20:09.200 --> 20:12.431
DANNY: Hey, Vic, you gotta sec?
I'll get on those rims.

20:12.640 --> 20:14.039
What's up?

20:14.240 --> 20:17.710
Uh, that guy from IAD got all over
me about department policy,

20:17.920 --> 20:19.672
disclosure of personal
relationships on the job.

20:19.880 --> 20:20.949
None of his business.

20:21.160 --> 20:23.515
Yeah, well, he's pushing me
really hard. Okay?

20:23.720 --> 20:26.154
I can't take a suspension
or a pay cut right now.

20:26.360 --> 20:29.272
I gotta notify Billings.
I just wanted you to know.

20:36.320 --> 20:38.276
When was the last time
you saw your sister?

20:38.480 --> 20:41.552
Lunchtime. She was gonna run out
for some soda, never came back.

20:41.760 --> 20:43.557
Your family drinks a lot of soda.

20:43.760 --> 20:46.797
I seem to remember you
were out for soda when
Lana Gregory was killed.

20:47.040 --> 20:50.669
CLAUDETTE:
It's only a few hours, grown woman.
Bit premature to call the police.

20:50.880 --> 20:54.270
I know my sister. She say
she be back, she be back.

20:54.480 --> 20:55.799
Mind if we look around?

20:56.000 --> 20:57.399
Wouldn't have called you if I did.

21:02.640 --> 21:04.790
CLAUDETTE:
I'll take her room, you take his.

21:11.920 --> 21:15.310
Fatima's room's clean. Back door's
unlocked. What do you have?

21:15.520 --> 21:16.873
It's what I don't have.

21:17.120 --> 21:22.752
Kleavon's death kit. Latex gloves,
knife, duct tape. It's gone.

21:23.920 --> 21:26.388
I was... I was here earlier.
What?

21:26.600 --> 21:28.636
It was spur of the moment.
Fatima gave her consent.

21:28.840 --> 21:31.354
You searched a murder suspect's
house without backup?

21:31.840 --> 21:33.910
What if Kleavon showed up?

21:34.120 --> 21:37.157
I hid in the closet. He didn't see me.
I slipped out the back door.

21:37.360 --> 21:39.828
If you're wrong, and he
confronted her after you left...

21:40.040 --> 21:42.713
I shouldn't have come alone, but
I wasn't sure you were up to it.

21:42.920 --> 21:44.876
Stress is a trigger, I saw you
were hurting this morning.

21:45.080 --> 21:46.877
I am fine.

21:48.360 --> 21:51.352
OFFICER: Got a neighbour
says he saw a prowler exiting
the backyard this morning,

21:51.560 --> 21:54.199
wearing what he called
"a hundred-dollar suit."

21:56.880 --> 21:59.075
I'll deal with the neighbour
if you think I'm up to it.

21:59.280 --> 22:01.316
Take Kleavon to the Barn,
get a statement.

22:01.520 --> 22:04.114
I paid over $300 for this suit.

22:08.440 --> 22:09.839
KAVANAUGH:
Hey.

22:12.600 --> 22:14.113
BECCA:
Who's this?

22:16.800 --> 22:20.395
It's Terry Crowley. He was
one of my guys, killed by a
drug dealer couple years ago.

22:20.600 --> 22:23.751
That is one version.
Terry was working for Justice,

22:23.960 --> 22:27.999
investigating allegations
of a relationship between
drug dealers and your clients.

22:28.200 --> 22:29.315
BECCA:
You have a different version?

22:29.520 --> 22:34.275
Detective Mackey, either acting alone
or with other members of his team,

22:34.480 --> 22:37.836
killed Detective Crowley or
put him in a position to be killed.

22:38.040 --> 22:41.919
Just like that Russian I was gonna
murder before you blew our sting?

22:42.120 --> 22:44.475
Any evidence or are you all attitude?

22:45.360 --> 22:47.271
In due course.

22:50.560 --> 22:52.357
These theatrics why
you wanted to see us?

22:52.560 --> 22:54.790
I'm sure the three of us
have better things to do.

22:55.000 --> 22:56.479
Yes.

22:57.280 --> 22:59.748
I'm officially informing you
you are under investigation

22:59.960 --> 23:03.111
for the death of Terry Crowley,
and other allegations of corruption.

23:03.320 --> 23:05.675
You have a right to
a PBA rep, to a lawyer.

23:06.360 --> 23:09.079
I see you already got one,
and a good one.

23:09.280 --> 23:12.590
Please, could you get him to initial
here and here, his signature there?

23:18.880 --> 23:22.634
BECCA:
We'll cooperate fully so you can stop
wasting everyone's time, lieutenant.

23:22.840 --> 23:24.068
I suppose you want a statement?

23:24.320 --> 23:27.676
Actually, if you could, uh,
have your clients walk me
through the house

23:27.880 --> 23:30.633
where Terry Crowley was killed,
that would be great.

23:31.040 --> 23:32.632
I'll arrange it soon.

23:32.840 --> 23:36.913
Oh, and take down these photos
or I'll file for harassment.

23:43.440 --> 23:44.509
Becca.

23:44.720 --> 23:47.473
Thought the headline in this case
was David against Goliath.

23:47.680 --> 23:50.035
Or did this murder charge
slip your mind?

23:50.240 --> 23:51.753
I can't talk about
this right now.

23:51.960 --> 23:53.279
[WHISPERS]
This is a big goddamn deal.

23:53.480 --> 23:57.029
It's all a lie. I'm sorry.
I'll call you later.

23:59.960 --> 24:00.949
What the hell's going on?

24:01.160 --> 24:02.832
He told them to bring me in.
Can you take the kids?

24:03.040 --> 24:04.268
You don't have to
talk to him, remember?

24:04.480 --> 24:05.549
I just wanna get this over with.

24:05.760 --> 24:07.159
He can't compel
your cooperation.

24:07.360 --> 24:09.920
If you feel uncomfortable
at any time, you just leave.

24:10.120 --> 24:11.189
Okay.

24:11.400 --> 24:13.391
Corrine. Thanks for coming.

24:14.640 --> 24:16.153
The children, they can wait inside.

24:16.360 --> 24:18.396
I can take care of my own kids.

24:18.600 --> 24:19.828
Okay.

24:20.320 --> 24:22.788
This way. Upstairs. Hey, guys.

24:24.000 --> 24:25.592
Dad, what the hell's going on?

24:25.800 --> 24:27.870
Don't talk like that.
He's a cop, right?

24:28.080 --> 24:30.833
Did Mom do something wrong?
No, never.

24:31.040 --> 24:31.995
Come on.
BILLINGS: Vic.

24:33.160 --> 24:36.914
I, uh, caught a 187 times two.
Need you to get on it.

24:37.120 --> 24:38.951
What's 187 mean?

24:39.160 --> 24:40.957
It means Dad's gonna
find you guys a ride.

24:41.160 --> 24:42.912
Come on, kids. Let's go.

24:43.440 --> 24:45.749
You need anything?
Can I get you something?
Coffee or water?

24:45.960 --> 24:47.757
Just ask your questions.

24:49.840 --> 24:54.277
You've told me that it's really
difficult to make both the tuitions.

24:54.480 --> 24:57.711
Yet Vic seems to be able to come up
with the money all the time.

24:58.760 --> 25:00.557
How do you think
he does that?

25:00.760 --> 25:01.988
Overtime.

25:02.200 --> 25:05.431
Yeah, I've checked those paystubs.

25:05.840 --> 25:08.991
He always has been a good
provider, wouldn't you say?

25:09.320 --> 25:12.869
I guess that might change
now that you have to split the pie

25:13.080 --> 25:14.308
four ways instead of three, huh?

25:14.520 --> 25:16.476
I don't understand.

25:17.560 --> 25:21.030
Oh, maybe you're not aware,

25:21.240 --> 25:24.198
Officer Danielle Sofer,
who works here,

25:24.400 --> 25:26.152
is filing paperwork admitting
to a sexual relationship

25:26.360 --> 25:29.557
with Vic over the last
couple of years.

25:31.520 --> 25:34.717
When did you get divorced?
Last year.

25:35.240 --> 25:36.753
Right.

25:36.960 --> 25:39.394
Officer Sofer is now pregnant.

25:41.160 --> 25:44.357
Is this another imaginary child
like Andy?

25:44.560 --> 25:47.518
I mean, what kind of a man
says he has an autistic child

25:47.720 --> 25:50.598
to a woman who has two
of her own? How sick is that?

25:50.800 --> 25:52.028
You know, I didn't
really like doing that.

25:52.240 --> 25:54.708
I'm sorry, I just needed to know
what kind of woman you are.

25:54.920 --> 25:56.638
Corrine...

25:56.840 --> 25:59.274
Really, I mean,
this is not about me.

25:59.480 --> 26:01.311
This is about Vic.

26:01.520 --> 26:06.878
It's about you, it's about the kids,
it's about this new baby,

26:07.560 --> 26:10.518
how we got to this place, and
where we're gonna go from here.

26:11.080 --> 26:12.479
Please.

26:13.520 --> 26:15.431
Have a seat?

26:17.520 --> 26:20.796
VIC:
"L.A." California.

26:21.720 --> 26:23.631
Same calibre as the Bop Street hit.
LEM: Yup.

26:23.840 --> 26:25.068
It's gotta be the shooter
from this morning.

26:25.280 --> 26:27.635
Payback's a bitch.
Yeah, and karma's a whore.

26:27.840 --> 26:30.434
Amado Alvaro. His place.
No sign of forced entry.

26:30.640 --> 26:32.949
What about ass-boy over there?
STAMOS: No ID yet.

26:33.160 --> 26:35.628
Neighbour called 911, saw
Alvaro's car driving away

26:35.840 --> 26:37.956
a little while after she
heard the gunshots.

26:38.160 --> 26:39.798
Hooptie? Gold rims?

26:40.000 --> 26:43.629
Yeah, '69 Olds Cutlass. Why?

26:43.840 --> 26:46.115
Run Alvaro's registration,
put an APB out on the car.

26:46.320 --> 26:47.719
Got it.

26:47.920 --> 26:49.990
Squad, let me get a run
on a '69 Olds Cutlass.

26:51.080 --> 26:54.516
OFFICER [ON RADIO]:
Vehicle should be rolling up to you
right now, detective. You see it?

26:54.720 --> 26:56.950
VIC:
We got it. Nice work, Larry.

26:57.160 --> 26:59.515
Say hello to whoever
killed L.A. and ass-boy.

26:59.720 --> 27:00.948
Who's the Chinaman?

27:01.160 --> 27:03.833
VIC:
I don't know, but we're
gonna find out.

27:04.680 --> 27:07.069
[TYRES SCREECHING]
[HORN HONKING]

27:07.280 --> 27:08.918
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

27:11.760 --> 27:13.318
Hey, you guys, hey!

27:15.840 --> 27:17.159
LEM:
Stop!

27:18.240 --> 27:19.559
Go.

27:20.360 --> 27:21.839
[GRUNTING]

27:23.560 --> 27:25.471
Stop.
SHANE: Hey.

27:26.440 --> 27:28.954
Halt.
Hold it.

27:29.320 --> 27:32.357
Hey, stop, dumb-ass.
It's a barbed-wire fence.

27:32.600 --> 27:34.272
LEM:
What the hell's he doing?

27:34.480 --> 27:36.038
[YELLS]

27:37.960 --> 27:39.871
[KANG GRUNTING]

27:42.040 --> 27:43.473
I didn't do nothing.

27:43.680 --> 27:45.398
Except a double homicide.

27:45.600 --> 27:47.113
That's crazy.
Amado's my main man.

27:47.360 --> 27:49.476
Funny how you know exactly
the murders we're talking about.

27:49.680 --> 27:52.513
We got you fleeing the scene
of a murder in the victim's car.

27:52.720 --> 27:54.711
You take one last look
at the outside world.

27:54.920 --> 27:56.399
Where'd you put
the murder weapon?

27:56.600 --> 27:58.033
They were dead when
I got there, I swear.

27:58.240 --> 28:00.037
All right, search the car.

28:00.240 --> 28:01.559
KANG:
He was into me for 10 grand.

28:02.080 --> 28:04.992
Some white guy named Kasper
was coming by to drop off money.

28:05.200 --> 28:06.918
[KANG PANTING]

28:07.120 --> 28:08.633
VIC:
Amado was meeting Kasper?

28:08.840 --> 28:11.877
I wasn't supposed to know.
Kasper was coming by to
pay him for some work he did.

28:12.080 --> 28:14.275
When I saw bodies, I bounced.

28:14.920 --> 28:17.480
We've gotta take
another run at Kasper.

28:18.760 --> 28:20.079
Remember Terry Crowley?

28:20.280 --> 28:22.191
CORRINE:
Sure, he was on Vic's team.

28:22.400 --> 28:26.473
Do you remember any change in Vic's
behaviour leading up to Terry's death?

28:26.680 --> 28:29.638
No, but he was pretty torn up
afterwards. We all were.

28:29.840 --> 28:32.354
I'm sure it was, uh, terrible.

28:35.760 --> 28:37.830
Terry was working for Justice,

28:38.040 --> 28:42.033
investigating your ex-husband's
team for corruption.

28:42.240 --> 28:46.119
Planting evidence, extortion,
kickbacks, laundry list of things.

28:48.200 --> 28:51.033
When Vic made Terry
as working for the feds,

28:51.240 --> 28:54.949
we believe that he and
Shane Vendrell murdered him.

28:56.760 --> 28:59.354
Vic's a lot of things,
but he's no killer.

28:59.560 --> 29:02.120
Vic is a survivor.
He'll do whatever it takes

29:02.320 --> 29:06.598
to protect himself,
his team and his family.

29:06.840 --> 29:09.718
Are you really trying to tell me
that after 12 years of marriage,

29:09.920 --> 29:11.558
you don't think that that man

29:11.760 --> 29:14.115
is capable of pulling
the trigger on someone

29:14.320 --> 29:17.153
who's trying to take away
everything from him? Everything?

29:17.360 --> 29:19.351
[CRYING]
You need to stop this, okay?

29:19.560 --> 29:20.595
Don't cry.

29:21.680 --> 29:25.958
I don't wanna see you
shed one single tear.

29:26.880 --> 29:30.429
Because tears imply
that you didn't know.

29:30.960 --> 29:35.033
And don't you sit here and tell me
that you didn't know, Mrs. Mackey.

29:36.400 --> 29:38.277
Twelve years you shared his bed.

29:38.480 --> 29:39.595
You knew.

29:39.800 --> 29:41.119
He paid your mortgage,

29:41.320 --> 29:44.437
he paid your bills, and now he's
